00:40:34.260 --> 00:40:36.660
A group that is staying together 

00:40:36.660 --> 00:40:39.460
and singing together and eating together. 

00:40:39.460 --> 00:40:43.260
They fish, that is what they do, their lives are about fish. 

00:40:43.260 --> 00:40:46.620
They are about the sea side. 
This is where they have been for years 

00:40:46.620 --> 00:40:48.220
and this is where they should be. 

00:40:49.860 --> 00:40:51.660
And they are going to keep this 

00:40:51.660 --> 00:40:53.260
for as long as they can. 

00:40:56.740 --> 00:40:59.340
That there seem to be less hamsi 

00:40:59.340 --> 00:41:02.180
makes these good times a bit sad too. 

00:41:03.900 --> 00:41:05.860
But the good feel of the people 

00:41:05.860 --> 00:41:08.900
and how proud they are of their ways makes you feel good too. 

00:41:11.140 --> 00:41:13.260
Turkey is huge. 

00:41:13.260 --> 00:41:15.500
I thought I knew it. 

00:41:15.500 --> 00:41:18.340
I thought I knew the land and its food. 

00:41:19.900 --> 00:41:21.580
I could not have been more wrong. 

00:41:24.100 --> 00:41:27.380
This is like a picture made of small special parts, 

00:41:27.380 --> 00:41:28.900
each with their own past. 

00:41:30.860 --> 00:41:33.820
I started this trip tasting the food of the kings 

00:41:33.820 --> 00:41:36.540
with its richness and how fancy it was. 

00:41:36.540 --> 00:41:39.020
That was a bit of a wrong idea, 

00:41:39.020 --> 00:41:41.460
because the real heart of the food here 

00:41:41.460 --> 00:41:43.420
is found in country parts. 

00:41:45.460 --> 00:41:48.980
It is different groups living quite close 

00:41:48.980 --> 00:41:51.580
but very, very different. 

00:41:51.580 --> 00:41:54.460
It is about keeping their old ways, their way of life. 

00:41:54.460 --> 00:41:55.860
Even their ways of talking. 

00:41:57.140 --> 00:41:59.300
It is also about keeping your food, 

00:41:59.300 --> 00:42:02.620
if it is fish, if it is milk food, 

00:42:02.620 --> 00:42:05.420
if it is fruit and plants. 

00:42:05.420 --> 00:42:07.980
But having fun with them when they are here, 

00:42:07.980 --> 00:42:11.020
and then, smart ways of keeping them for the winter, 

00:42:11.020 --> 00:42:14.340
for the dark days when there is very little else. 

00:42:14.340 --> 00:42:17.500
This is a truly different Turkey from the one I thought I would see 

00:42:17.500 --> 00:42:19.180
when I got off that plane. 
